cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel network architecture to address the information imbalance problem in object detection, which involves combining spatial and semantic information in different layers of the network. This is a problem that requires a combination of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also involves designing a fusing module to combine features from different parts of the network, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
